title: Gaza Ceasefire In Doubt After Israel Kills 19 Palestinians In Air Strikes | 10 News
description: Three weeks after being signed, the Gaza ceasefire could be on the verge of collapsing, with at least 19 Palestinians killed in Israeli air strikes. The attacks were sparked after Hamas returned the remains of a hostage whose body was already recovered two years ago in what Israel has described as a clear breach of the ceasefire conditions. title: Medicare Bulk Billing Overhaul, Fawlty Towers Star Remembered, Queensland Exam Blunder | 10 News+
description: Australians will enjoy cheaper visits to the doctor starting November 1, when a multibillion-dollar overhaul of the Medicare bulk billing system comes into effect. GP clinics will be offered more financial incentives if they provide free appointments to any Medicare card holder. For women, the federal government scheme also includes larger rebates for menopause health assessments and long-term contraceptives.  Revered 'Fawlty Towers' actress Prunella Scales, known for her hilariously deadpan portrayla of Sybil, has died aged 93. Her witty performance as the hotel's matron, alongside her bumbling husband, played by John Cleese, cemented Scales as a bastion of dry British humor.   Queensland’s curriculum authority has been put on notice by the state’s Education Minister, as the number of high schools involved in a major teaching blunder has risen to nine. 140 Ancient History students across the state were taught about the Ancient Roman Emperor Augustus Caesar, instead of his grand-uncle and predecessor Julius Caesar. title: Category 3 Hurricane Melissa Leaves Trail of Destruction Across Cuba’s Southeast | 10 News
description: Severe flash flooding is being reported in Cuba tonight, after the country’s southeast took a direct hit from the eye of Hurricane Melissa.  These are the latest pictures from Cuba’s second-largest city — released by the state-run broadcaster.  Melissa made landfall as a Category 3 storm, packing winds of up to 193 kilometres an hour. It comes after the hurricane tore through Jamaica, where a state of disaster has now been declared. title: Jamaica Declared Disaster Zone As Hurricane Melissa Rips Through Cuba | 10 News
description: The devastation of Hurricane Melissa on Jamaica has become clearer, as the nation is declared as a disaster zone while the storm moves on to Cuba.  Melissa has been declared Jamaica's strongest ever storm on record, with four people confirmed dead in the country, while dozens have been killed in Haiti.  Eyewitness accounts show the flooding in Cuba's Holguin Province following Melissa's passage through the region.  Hundreds of Cuban rural communities have been isolated, while the city of Santiago was also heavily hit.
